page.title: 09TEIGNMOUTH'S POPULATION
page.content: The biggest percentage of under 16's are situated in the West of Teigmouth e.g. from Bitton House to Kingsway. This is because W. Teignmouth is mainly occupied by families. The largest amount of old age pensioners live in the East of Teignmouth, but closely followed by the Central and North areas. The largest percentage of cars per household is found in the Northern part of the town. This is because the Northern part has less unemployment. The largest percentage of unemployment is found in the Western part of Teignmouth. The most privately owned houses are in the East and North parts and the Western area contains most of the council houses and flats.
